@Jmcgloin: the way the class is defined, it will __not__ work _even __after___ you import the package. Since it doesn't have the `public` modifier, by default it's "package protected": it can only be accessed from within the same package (could be another class, though).

In order to be able to call it from another package you need to _explicitly_ define the class as `public`.

